application.model

Class Park

  • java.lang.Object
    • application.model.Park

  • public class Park
extends java.lang.Object
    The Park class represents a real world park with a finite number of zones. Uses Zone and Dinosaur classes. Each Park class has a name and utilizes a HashMap to store zones as keys and ArrayLists of Dinosaurs as a value. Each Park class has the following methods: Override of Object.toString(), loadZones, loadDinosaurs, relocate, save, findZoneName, dinoExists, and zoneExists. Accessors and Mutators are the following: getParkName, setParkName, getParkMap, setParkMap and getZone.
    Author:
    Ivy Vasquez Sandoval (egi444) UTSA CS 3443 - Lab 8 Spring 2019
